It's linked to the model and tao you have staked, the hardware just needs to support the fact that the model needs to run.

For validators, you need to have hardware capable of sending as much messages as possible. They only run 1 model, so the hardware requirements are not that big compared to miners. However, their income is relative to the amount of Tao staked and used on the network. More staked Tao means more income, until they hit the "glass ceiling" (which is proportional to the amount of stake divided to the total tao staked on the network).

For miners, you need 2 things: A model that helps the validators get their loss down (lower loss == better rank), and a server that is capable of replying with the correct answer within a block (12 sec). Currently you can do this with a good set of CPU power, however as the developers increase the input, so does the amount of CPU power required, until it reaches a point where CPU miners are not feasible. Some use GPU just to prevent them from encountering this exact reason (eventually it will be cheaper to rent a GPU vs a CPU).
